question.title: What internal challenges do you face in delivering a better customer experience? (Select all that apply)
What do you think are the key risks of ignoring NPS?

answers.value: Ignoring NPS can be detrimental as you will never know what and how users feel when they are using the product

question.title: How do you see your role in UX/CX evolving in the next 3–5 years?

answers.value: I do see these becoming more significant in discussion when it comes to the productisation stage, with the teams involved earlier and with more autonomy given.

question.title:
Have you ever used UX research or design to improve NPS?

If yes, briefly describe the initiative.

answers.value: Yes, we used UXR to understand the types of interfaces and options that users are more inclined to, from there we do a reverse engineering of whether it matches business goals

question.title: What methods have you used to improve customer loyalty/satisfaction? (eg. Run usability testing, analyse customer feedback from CS tickets and NPS)

answers.value: Run usability test, gather feedback during launch and also post launch feedback
